title: Youth football: Little Warriors run past Lowell
text: Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 10:33 AM   8, 2015 at 10:33 AM   weekend's play for the Little Warriors.   Pee Wee A The Little Warriors combined   of offense and scored six touchdowns, beating Lowell, Mass., 44-18 last Saturday for their fourth straight win. Chris Capezzuto ran for 120 yards and scored two touchdowns, while Matt Alkire ran for two touchdowns on 50 yards. Liam Considine scored on a 5-yard quarterback sneak, and also threw a 30-yard touchdown pass to Owen Bateman. All scores were made possible by the blocking from a solid offense line led by Kolby Blaisdell,   Tyler Parkinson. Defensively, Nico Zaino led the Warriors with six tackles, while Joe Larrabee, Colin Harrington and Jack McCann all had five, and Levon McCann had four. The Little Warriors host Timberlane on Saturday at Winnacunnet High School at 9 a.m.   4-0 on the season after a 36-0 win over Lowell, Mass. last Saturday. Jake Fredericks, Brylan Knowles, Aidan McErlain, Gavin Coates and Frank Brown each scored a touchdown for the Little Warriors. Brown and Lebron Miller each caught a 2-point conversion pass from quarterback Conor Fenlon. The offensive line consisted of Miller, Quinn MacNeil, Jason Pinsonnault, Ben Goodwin, Brandon Matheson, Tony Johnson, and Nolan Perkins. Defensively, Perkins, Miller, Brown, Coner Blaisdell, James Robillard, Pinsonnault, Matthew Mattimore, Fredericks and MacNeil stood out. The Little Warriors host Timberlane on Saturday at Winnacunnet High School at 10:30 a.m. By Staff Reports
